On November 2, 2017, Vice President Mike Pence visited Correct Craft, a boat manufacturing company in Orlando, Florida, to discuss President Trump's plans for tax cuts. Pence emphasized the importance of tax cuts for working families, small businesses, and family farms. He also discussed the need for simplifying the tax code and lowering corporate tax rates. Pence and the attendees discussed the potential impact of tax cuts on job creation and economic growth. They also highlighted the need to repeal the estate tax and bring back profits trapped overseas. Pence urged the attendees to support tax cuts and to voice their opinions to elected representatives.